<!-- Parallel execution by methods

This may fail if WebDriver is not thread-safe.

Reason:
- parallel="methods" runs multiple test methods in parallel within the same <test> tag
- If a single WebDriver instance is shared across threads, it leads to conflicts
- Multiple threads try to control the same browser at the same time

Result:
- Tests become unstable (flaky)
- Unexpected failures occur

Solution:
- Use ThreadLocal WebDriver to create separate driver instances per thread

-->